Usage: PLAYBACK [-R] [pattern]
  Shows away file without setting you back

  Plays back stored messages without marking you as not being away.
  If -R is passed as an argument, messages will be played in
  reverse order. Optional pattern may include * and ?. If used,
  only entries matching pattern will be shown.

See also:
  AWAYENCR
  AWAYT
  REMLOG
  SETAWAY
  SETBACK
  SHOWAWAY
